Sensitivity Analysis is when you change one number in your problem and see how it is going to change the outcome you already recieved. Say you had to choose how many of one product to produce to maximize your profit. You go through and plug in all your numbers and get a final outcome. Then you go back and change one of the numbers of the products that you are going to produce and see how it effects your final outcome, that is what the sensitivity analysis does. It is important because if you went though and tried different senarios you could possibly find the best way to maximize your profits. 
	SolverTable is a add-in on excell that you can plug in your input cell, changing cells, and contraints and it will solve the problem for you. It goes through and finds the best possible outcome whether you are trying to maximize your profit or minimize your cost.
